Here's the bash script I use with Mercurial to deploy:<p>hg qpop -a ; 
hg pull ; 
hg update $1 ; 
hg qpush -a<p>The $1 is a branch or tag argument given to the Bash script. That way you can easily specify a particular version to update to (or rollback to!) on the command line.<p>The qpop and qpush will rebase any MQ patches you've made, e.g. local configuration changes, hacks, etc.<p>More on rebasing applied patches with Mercurial: <a href="http://hgbook.red-bean.com/hgbookch12.html#x16-28900012.8" rel="nofollow">http://hgbook.red-bean.com/hgbookch12.html#x16-28900012.8</a>
